  "game:characterclass-bcinnkeeper": "Innkeeper",
  "game:characterdesc-bcinnkeeper": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Stoke the fire, fill the cups, bar the door for the night. One day every tale will fall silent, yet the hearth will still burn for the next traveler.</i></font><br><br>Innkeepers can prepare more nourishing and valuable meals, turning simple ingredients into proper food. However, they grow hungry faster and are less skilled at gathering wild plants.",
  "game:characterclass-bcminer": "Miner",
  "game:characterdesc-bcminer": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Swing the pick, follow the vein, delve ever deeper. One day the mountain will claim you, yet others will still seek its hidden treasures beneath the stone.</i></font><br><br>Miners gather more ore and stone, efficiently uncovering the riches buried beneath the earth. However, they lack skill in archery and struggle with both plants and animals.",
  "game:characterclass-bctraveler": "Traveler",
  "game:characterdesc-bctraveler": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Walk onward. Find a place to call home. Leave it behind and continue your journey. One day you will die beside a distant road, and no one will know where you came from.</i></font><br><br>Travelers move quickly and are skilled at finding wild plants and long-forgotten artifacts. However, life on the road leaves them weaker in combat and less resilient.",
  "game:characterclass-bctailor": "Tailor",
  "game:characterdesc-bctailor": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Thread the needle. Mend a torn coat. Return it to its owner. One day they will die from cold, age, or steel, and you will sew another for someone else.</i></font><br><br>Tailors craft better clothing, providing greater comfort and protection in harsh conditions. However, they are less hardy and less capable when caring for animals.",
  "game:characterclass-bcknight": "Knight",
  "game:characterdesc-bcknight": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Sharpen your sword. Slay your enemy. Return to those you love. In time they will be gone, and you will still be fighting for people whose names you do not know.</i></font><br><br>Knights deal heavy damage and possess greater endurance, making them formidable in direct combat. The price of their strength is greater hunger and poor skill with crops.",
  "game:characterclass-bcblacksmith": "Blacksmith",
  "game:characterdesc-bcblacksmith": "<font color=\"#99c9f9\"><i>Heat the steel. Shape it with your hands. Brand it with your mark. One day no one will remember your name, yet the marks of your hammer will remain on the blades of other men.</i></font><br><br>Blacksmiths create stronger and more effective tools, drawing true value from every piece of metal. However, years spent at the forge make them slower and quicker to hunger.",
  "game:traitname-bcwildfood": "Wild food",
  "game:trait-bcwildfood": "<font color=\"#84ff84\">• Wild food </font>",
